column1: NOTE: All surface water temperatures were taken right after the sun rose before it hit the water

column2: Windy and sunny.  First day loon on nest.
Windy - snagged and lost Secchi disc.

Sunny and breezy.  We have two nesting loons on the lower reservoir.  Today when we went past one she was off the nest.  There are two eggs. Sunny and breezy.  We have two nesting loons on the lower reservoir.  Today when we went past one she was off the nest.  There are two eggs.

column1: Also we have a nesting pair of eagles every year who pick off a few of the mallard ducklings each year.  We also have an osprey.

column2: water choppy with boat activity. Water temp: 78 deg.
calmest day all summer- hence the deeper reading. Water temp: 77.2 water was exceptionally calm- hence the deeper reading. Water temp: 77.2 absolutely dead calm- hence deeper reading. Water temp:77.2
Sunny and calm.  One loon on lake and young eagle spotted in channel between lower and upper Reservoir.

Slightly overcast and some wind.  One Loon observed on nest with mate nearby.  Also saw another nest with nothing on it.  There is a third nest with a loon on it with a mate nearby observed on May 24th. Slightly overcast and some wind.  One Loon observed on nest with mate nearby.  Also saw another nest with nothing on it.  There is a third nest with a loon on it with a mate nearby observed on May 24th.
Beautiful- sunny and calm.  Loons spotted- two adults and one baby.  They had two babies shortly after July 4th.
water temp: 74.  Sixteen loons in a group spotted.
water temp at 3 feet: 72 degrees- 60 at 10 feet.
choppy wave action. water temp was 76 degrees 3 feet down.
water temp 3 feet down: 67 degrees. Choppy water
water slightly discolored. Water temp: 76 degrees.
water slightly discolored- somewhat greenish. Water temp 3 ft down: 78 deg.
water temp. 3 ft down: 75 degrees. Saw 2 loons with 1 chick.
water temp@3feet: 78 deg. overcast and calm.
Choppy water. Water temp. 82 deg. three feet down.

lake entirely tannin-colored brownish yellow. grass-type weeds- many with the root systems attached- floating everywhere making boating a challenge. Shorelines reek of dead snails- identified as Banded and Chinese Mystery snails. Warm temps and water probable cause of the above. Water temp at 3 ft is 82.6 but was 86 deg. yesterday.
water temp three ft. down: 79. Water still stained a yellowish brown. Surface water full of masses of floating grass-like weeds- making navigation a challenge.
water temp. 3ft deep: 70deg. Very windy and choppy conditions.
overcast and slightly choppy. four very new baby loons spotted.
perfect conditions. Water temp 3' down is 77 deg. Three pair of baby loons for sure.
slight chop on water but full sunlight
water temp. 3 ft down: 71 deg. Very windy conditions. Two newly hatched loon chicks observed.
conditions could not be better. Water temp. 3 ft down: 77 deg.
beautiful conditions. water temp. 3 ft. deep: 77 deg.
two loons (immature) spotted in the area.
water temp: 56 deg. Observed two loons in the bay.
water temp 3 ft. down: 69.9. very calm water.
water temp.74 deg. Overcast but sunny.
water temp: 76 deg. Slight chop on water.
water temp: 78 deg. water is clear with great abundance of floating vegetation.
water temp 3ft deep: 63 deg. no loons observed on entire lake.
recent heavy rains have resulted in pollen and other debris in water. Also- wind was churning the surface.
observed a loon with baby on lower Resevoir Pond.Water temp 79 deg.
best conditions all summer. Water temp. 3 ft deep: 71 deg. One adult loon observed.
water temp three feet deep: 71 deg. Adult loon with baby observed.
